Modifications in this fork (high-level):
- TETRA fleet release pipeline (.github/workflows/{ci,release-image}.yml) for
  automated `:latest` and tag-driven `:stable` / `:<version>` publication on
  ghcr.io/tetra-2023/open-webui-mcp.
- CONTRIBUTING.md documents the upstream-bump procedure (re-pin SHA, re-audit,
  rebuild) so the spec snapshot stays aligned with the running OpenWebUI.
- scripts/check-spec-drift.sh — runtime helper to diff the bundled OpenAPI
  snapshot against a live OpenWebUI's /openapi.json before deciding to bump.
- README.md, CHANGELOG.md, SECURITY.md adapted for TETRA fleet conventions.
- patches/specs/open-webui.openapi.json — TETRA-side OpenAPI snapshot applied
  at image build (Dockerfile COPY) to overwrite the upstream-bundled spec
  when upstream's pinned SHA lags the OWUI version we deploy. Tag suffix
  `-N` (e.g., 0.2.2-1) marks releases that ship such a downstream-only patch
  on top of an unchanged upstream pin.

No source-level changes to the wrapper itself — all of `src/openwebui_mcp/`
is byte-identical to the imported commit.

This repository is intentionally disconnected from upstream — there is no
GitHub fork relationship. A local `upstream` git remote pointing at
stephanschielke/open-webui-mcp-server can be configured for occasional manual
cherry-picks of upstream changes.
